      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, a pinnacle of 90s JDM engineering. This example features the legendary 13B-REW rotary engine, maintaining factory-spec compression across all chambers. The sequential twin-turbocharger system delivers a linear torque curve with seamless transition, managed by a pristine factory vacuum line network. Chassis dynamics are uncompromised, retaining the original lightweight aluminum double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential for optimal power delivery. The 50/50 weight distribution and low polar moment of inertia remain as sharp as the day it left Hiroshima. Finished in its original paint with no signs of thermal degradation in the engine bay and zero oxidation on the undercarriage. A true turn-key investment for the discerning collector.",
